        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 6:23AM CDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 623 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hillsview, or 9 miles north of Bowdle, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hosmer and Hillsview.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
